01:04:53,680 --> 01:04:55,040
Which is why,

787
01:04:55,040 --> 01:04:58,240
you should've taken those pictures with them.

788
01:04:58,240 --> 01:04:59,960
Then you'll have had evidence to support your claims.

789
01:05:00,760 --> 01:05:02,680
Back then??

790
01:05:02,680 --> 01:05:06,560
I gave no meaning to those who passed me by.

791
01:05:06,560 --> 01:05:07,480
But now,

792
01:05:08,120 --> 01:05:10,560
looking at the pictures with you, like this??

793
01:05:11,720 --> 01:05:15,400
I'm starting to regret not having left any of their traces behind.

794
01:05:18,160 --> 01:05:19,800
Then how about you do so now?

795
01:05:20,800 --> 01:05:22,160
With that camera.

796
01:05:27,040 --> 01:05:29,000
Hyun-joong got his honorary graduation certificate,

797
01:05:29,000 --> 01:05:30,840
but he never took a photo.

798
01:05:30,840 --> 01:05:33,040
Let's call everyone up and take a picture together.

799
01:05:33,040 --> 01:05:34,080
I'll take it for you.

800
01:05:52,440 --> 01:05:55,800
This is my first time taking a photo. Will I show up?

801
01:05:55,800 --> 01:05:56,960
You will.

802
01:05:56,960 --> 01:05:58,720
I once tried with my cellphone.

803
01:05:59,560 --> 01:06:02,440
We all should've put on some more blush.

804
01:06:02,440 --> 01:06:04,080
Everyone's so pale that anyone will be able to tell we're ghosts!

805
01:06:05,040 --> 01:06:08,360
It's alright. What if they do?

806
01:06:09,520 --> 01:06:12,800
Hyun-joong, keep your mouth closed when we take the photo.

807
01:06:12,800 --> 01:06:15,360
And Mr. Kim, don't close your eyes.

808
01:06:20,920 --> 01:06:21,640
Alright.

809
01:06:22,960 --> 01:06:24,600
Here we go.

810
01:06:24,600 --> 01:06:27,920
One, two, three!

811
01:06:40,320 --> 01:06:42,040
Mr. Koo, hurry up and join us.

812
01:06:42,040 --> 01:06:43,720
Join us!

813
01:06:43,720 --> 01:06:44,920
Come stand here, Mr. Koo.

814
01:07:25,080 --> 01:07:27,560
How am I supposed to put that away if you're sitting on it?

815
01:07:27,560 --> 01:07:28,640
Hurry up and move.

816
01:07:30,000 --> 01:07:31,040
Lift me up and carry me.

817
01:07:33,840 --> 01:07:35,320
I said, carry me!

818
01:07:35,320 --> 01:07:37,040
If you won't, I won't move.

819
01:07:37,040 --> 01:07:38,440
Forget it.

820
01:07:38,440 --> 01:07:39,480
You put it away, then.

821
01:07:46,400 --> 01:07:47,960
Off to my room!

822
01:08:03,080 --> 01:08:05,560
Now that we took that photo, let's go for black bean noodles.

823
01:08:09,760 --> 01:08:10,800
Ugh!

824
01:08:15,840 --> 01:08:17,080
You guys took a photo.

825
01:08:17,680 --> 01:08:19,680
Everyone had a lot of fun.

826
01:08:20,600 --> 01:08:23,000
You should've called me, too.

827
01:08:23,000 --> 01:08:27,120
We just thought we should take it together

828
01:08:27,120 --> 01:08:30,320
before President Jang leaves and the hotel disappears.

829
01:08:30,320 --> 01:08:33,080
The hotel will disappear? Why?

830
01:08:33,080 --> 01:08:38,000
Old Mago is building another lunar inn.

831
01:08:39,680 --> 01:08:43,960
Once that happens, President Jang's Del Luna??

832
01:08:43,960 --> 01:08:45,200
will be gone.

833
01:08:45,200 --> 01:08:46,240
Then what about you?

834
01:08:47,600 --> 01:08:50,920
Once the hotel disappears, will you be gone, too?

835
01:09:22,440 --> 01:09:24,960
It's coming along nicely.

836
01:09:27,480 --> 01:09:29,400
I hear Old Mago is brewing new wine for

837
01:09:29,400 --> 01:09:31,640
the next owner.

838
01:09:32,320 --> 01:09:34,000
I'll drink that, and be the owner.

839
01:09:34,000 --> 01:09:36,840
It's Old Mago who decides on that.

840
01:09:36,840 --> 01:09:38,400
Then why not have President Jang have a sip of it again,

841
01:09:38,400 --> 01:09:40,040
and continue to be the owner here?

842
01:09:40,040 --> 01:09:43,080
Do you think she'll do that? When she's finally set her free?

843
01:09:44,120 --> 01:09:45,800
Then when's Old Mago coming?

844
01:09:45,800 --> 01:09:47,000
Or where can I find her?

845
01:09:47,000 --> 01:09:50,280
She's not just someone you can meet just because you wish to.

846
01:09:50,280 --> 01:09:52,160
Then no one here can meet her?

847
01:09:53,680 --> 01:09:57,880
It seems Mr. Koo was given permission to enter her apothecary.

848
01:09:57,880 --> 01:10:01,240
He said he brought the firefly from that place.

849
01:10:26,360 --> 01:10:28,160
(Apothecary - 11-28 Yakjae-golmokgil Gyeongdong Market)

850
01:10:32,560 --> 01:10:34,160
- Cheers! - Cheers!

851
01:10:38,000 --> 01:10:40,800
Sanchez, thank you for everything so far.

852
01:10:40,800 --> 01:10:43,880
Let's have dinner sometime with Chan-sung. It's on me.

853
01:10:43,880 --> 01:10:45,440
Are you moving back with your parents' place?

854
01:10:46,280 --> 01:10:47,560
She's coming to my place.

855
01:10:48,240 --> 01:10:50,120
You guys will be living together, I see!

856
01:10:50,920 --> 01:10:52,800
You're in for a tough road ahead, Young-soo.

857
01:10:53,280 --> 01:10:55,960
While Mi-ra does try to help around the house,

858
01:10:55,960 --> 01:10:57,880
she's totally useless.

859
01:10:58,440 --> 01:11:00,200
I'm already aware of that.

860
01:11:00,200 --> 01:11:02,080
We've already fought so much that

861
01:11:02,080 --> 01:11:05,800
we're now going to test our limit by sticking around 24/7.

862
01:11:05,800 --> 01:11:08,720
Thankfully, I'm tidy.

863
01:11:08,720 --> 01:11:12,320
And if not anything else, Mi-ra's a great cook.

864
01:11:14,080 --> 01:11:15,400
Mi-ra?

865
01:11:15,400 --> 01:11:16,480
Yes.

866
01:11:17,080 --> 01:11:20,520
The kimchi and side dishes she brought me were delicious.

867
01:11:21,720 --> 01:11:24,920
Well, I didn't make all of that??

868
01:11:24,920 --> 01:11:26,960
My parents helped me out a bit.

869
01:11:26,960 --> 01:11:28,080
Oh.

870
01:11:28,080 --> 01:11:31,200
I guess you're not lying. They are from their factory, yes.

871
01:11:31,200 --> 01:11:32,360
Factory?

872
01:11:33,560 --> 01:11:36,880
My parents run a kimchi factory.

873
01:11:38,080 --> 01:11:39,880
It's advertised a lot on homeshopping channels.

874
01:11:39,880 --> 01:11:40,960
You've never heard of Daeho Kimchi?

875
01:11:40,960 --> 01:11:43,040
Daeho Kimchi?

876
01:11:43,040 --> 01:11:46,040
Wow, I only ever ate that brand when I lived by myself.

877
01:11:46,040 --> 01:11:51,200
So that's why your side dishes suit my palate perfectly!

878
01:11:51,200 --> 01:11:53,040
No wonder.

879
01:11:53,040 --> 01:11:56,800
So the side dishes that you grew up on were made by my parents!

880
01:11:57,920 --> 01:12:00,080
We really must be destined for each other.

881
01:12:00,080 --> 01:12:01,600
You're right.

882
01:12:01,600 --> 01:12:04,440
But both Chan-sung and I eat that kimchi,

883
01:12:04,440 --> 01:12:07,000
as well as some tens of thousands in this country??

884
01:12:07,000 --> 01:12:09,080
So I really wouldn't call it destiny??

885
01:12:09,080 --> 01:12:11,760
Young-soo said it suits his palate perfectly!

886
01:12:11,760 --> 01:12:13,960
- Right? - Of course.

887
01:12:13,960 --> 01:12:15,200
- How about we do a cheer? - Cheers!

888
01:12:16,240 --> 01:12:17,600
- A love shot? - Love shot!

889
01:12:17,600 --> 01:12:18,840
Hey, we just clicked!

890
01:12:21,480 --> 01:12:24,360
Right, I should be hoping that they get along until she leaves.

891
01:12:24,360 --> 01:12:26,200
What if they have another fight and she doesn't leave, right?

892
01:12:30,040 --> 01:12:32,080
- Good? - Good!

893
01:12:35,680 --> 01:12:38,080
I take it that you're both writers.

894
01:12:38,080 --> 01:12:41,200
This is Yi Tae-baek's favorite wine.

895
01:12:42,480 --> 01:12:46,280
On my left is a bestselling author,

896
01:12:46,280 --> 01:12:48,720
who passed away before publishing his newest work.

897
01:12:48,720 --> 01:12:50,880
It's a pity.

898
01:12:50,880 --> 01:12:55,080
I'd done a lot of research, and the story was interesting.

899
01:12:55,080 --> 01:12:57,040
What kind of a novel were you working on?

900
01:12:57,040 --> 01:12:59,520
It's about a scholar from the Joseon Dynasty.

901
01:13:00,800 --> 01:13:03,200
Our bartender here is also a scholar who came first

902
01:13:03,200 --> 01:13:05,120
on the state examination.

903
01:13:05,120 --> 01:13:06,800
Is that right?

904
01:13:06,800 --> 01:13:08,920
May I ask what your name is?

905
01:13:08,920 --> 01:13:11,560
It's not a name that was recorded in history??

906
01:13:11,560 --> 01:13:14,400
The protagonist of my story had also ranked first

907
01:13:14,400 --> 01:13:17,120
on the state examinations.

908
01:13:17,120 --> 01:13:20,240
However, this was later revoked.

909
01:13:20,240 --> 01:13:22,200
Did that really happen?

910
01:13:22,200 --> 01:13:24,560
He'd been the author of some rather obscene books,

911
01:13:24,560 --> 01:13:26,520
so when he was exposed, he was heavily criticized

912
01:13:26,520 --> 01:13:28,000
and had his acceptance revoked.

913
01:13:28,000 --> 01:13:30,000
It was a story about a perverted scholar.

914
01:13:31,280 --> 01:13:33,360
How interesting.

915
01:13:33,360 --> 01:13:36,120
What is the name of this perverted scholar?

916
01:13:36,120 --> 01:13:37,720
He had quite a grand name.

917
01:13:37,720 --> 01:13:40,640
Si-ik, meaning 'The Wings of Our Time.'

918
01:13:40,640 --> 01:13:43,000
His name is Kim Si-ik.

919
01:13:49,160 --> 01:13:52,480
If you have any shame, Kim Si-ik,

920
01:13:52,480 --> 01:13:55,080
don't ever hold your head up high again!

921
01:13:58,880 --> 01:14:01,440
I did complete my work, however,

922
01:14:01,440 --> 01:14:04,120
so it may still be published posthumously.

923
01:14:04,680 --> 01:14:07,000
I really do hope it does.

924
01:14:35,120 --> 01:14:38,600
I hear she brewed wine containing the essence of the moon.

925
01:14:46,120 --> 01:14:48,360
It's back to how it was.

926
01:14:49,520 --> 01:14:52,160
No, it's different from then.

927
01:14:52,880 --> 01:14:56,000
Back then, I'd been fixed in time

928
01:14:56,000 --> 01:14:59,440
but this time, time started flowing again

929
01:14:59,440 --> 01:15:03,120
to sprout leaves and bloom flowers.

930
01:15:06,040 --> 01:15:12,160
Are you hoping it may sprout and bloom, once again?

931
01:15:19,400 --> 01:15:21,040
This tree is dead now.

932
01:15:22,000 --> 01:15:24,080
If I were to hope for another period of time like that,

933
01:15:25,800 --> 01:15:27,200
I'd have to cross the Styx.

934
01:15:29,000 --> 01:15:30,200
Yes, you're right.

935
01:15:33,240 --> 01:15:36,160
Yu-na, what is it?

936
01:15:39,280 --> 01:15:40,360
President Jang??

937
01:15:41,120 --> 01:15:45,000
I stole the wine from Old Mago's apothecary.

938
01:15:51,040 --> 01:15:53,200
I heard this wine is for the new owner.

939
01:15:55,520 --> 01:15:57,960
President Jang, please drink this again

940
01:15:59,080 --> 01:16:01,000
and remain at this hotel.

941
01:16:26,680 --> 01:16:29,480
The girl who frequents your hotel has

942
01:16:29,480 --> 01:16:32,120
stolen my lunar wine.

943
01:16:33,120 --> 01:16:35,880
She probably did it out of the fear of losing Hyun-joong,

944
01:16:35,880 --> 01:16:37,600
our frontman.

945
01:16:37,600 --> 01:16:39,720
She didn't want the hotel to disappear.

946
01:16:39,720 --> 01:16:44,000
Then she probably took it to Jang Man-wol.

947
01:16:47,360 --> 01:16:50,040
If Man-wol drinks that

948
01:16:50,040 --> 01:16:52,320
and regains the power of the lunar tree??

949
01:16:52,320 --> 01:16:54,400
Hotel Del Luna will go on,

950
01:16:56,400 --> 01:17:00,960
and you two will be able to remain together.

951
01:17:05,000 --> 01:17:07,000
If Ms. Jang Man-wol makes such a choice??

952
01:17:08,080 --> 01:17:09,440
Will you not stop her?

953
01:17:12,360 --> 01:17:14,440
I thought you wanted to send her off well.

954
01:17:17,720 --> 01:17:20,040
If I won't stop her,

955
01:17:20,960 --> 01:17:23,920
what will you do?

956
01:17:40,240 --> 01:17:42,080
Mr. Koo, Yu-na??

957
01:17:42,080 --> 01:17:45,080
I know. Where is Ms. Jang Man-wol now?

958
01:18:11,560 --> 01:18:14,360
On the night I was first tied to the lunar tree

959
01:18:17,480 --> 01:18:20,280
shined a big full moon, just like now.

960
01:18:28,280 --> 01:18:32,080
And now, the wine I had then has found its way back to me.

961
01:18:37,680 --> 01:18:39,080
Koo Chan-sung.

962
01:18:43,680 --> 01:18:45,600
Should I drink this wine again?

963
01:19:00,120 --> 01:19:02,040
When I went back in time

964
01:19:03,400 --> 01:19:06,120
and met you,

965
01:19:06,120 --> 01:19:08,640
I wanted to take the drink you offered me

966
01:19:08,640 --> 01:19:10,640
and remain by your side.

967
01:19:16,640 --> 01:19:17,960
If I had done that,

968
01:19:19,000 --> 01:19:21,200
I may have been your 85th passerby

969
01:19:22,560 --> 01:19:25,000
and painted a portrait for you.

970
01:19:41,520 --> 01:19:44,080
But as I was hanging the picture we took together,

971
01:19:47,000 --> 01:19:51,200
I told myself I will be your 99th and your final general manager.

972
01:19:53,640 --> 01:19:58,440
I won't let you go through another meaningless 100th cycle.

973
01:20:11,600 --> 01:20:13,040
So??

974
01:20:16,080 --> 01:20:17,640
Please don't drink that.

975
01:20:28,080 --> 01:20:30,520
I knew you'd tell me that.

976
01:21:45,080 --> 01:21:46,480
Thanks, Koo Chan-sung.

977
01:22:01,520 --> 01:22:02,920
I love you.

978
01:22:15,840 --> 01:22:17,120
I love you.
